    </activity>
    
    <p>
    In <xref ref="ssec_primeIdeals" text="title"/> and <xref ref="ssec_maximalIdeals" text="title"/>, 
    we will explore the question of when <m>R/I</m> possesses some of the properties we've previously explored, 
    e.g., when is <m>R/I</m> a domain? A field? First, we conclude with two explorations. The first gives us a 
    sense of what these rings can look like. The second connects quotient rings 
    to <em>solution sets</em> of polynomial equations.
    </p>
    
